voice_to_text: Uh, there was a point in my life where I was homeless, and there was a point in my life when I couldn't afford food. Same time, obviously. Uh, and you know who fed me the most? Arabs and Arab men. Specifically. The people that treated me with the most respect, the most consistent respect, and the most kindness were Arabs. Specifically Arab men. I knew that if I begged in the fancier white area that I could get to, in the area near the commuter trains, nobody acknowledged I existed. They walked by me, they didn't see me. And if you can't afford to give someone something and you don't wanna make eye contact, whatever. I'm not here to please. How you interact with people. But these are people I knew could give. These are people I would see go in and pull out a lot of money, and I'll be like, hey, can you buy me something? They be like, I don't have money. And it's like, okay, whatever. Like, you don't have to give me anything. But they never would. Like, they rarely would. But I could walk not too far away and go into an Arab neighborhood with Arab restaurants and Arab shops, and I didn't even have to ask. I could walk through the neighborhoods and people would be like, do you need to eat? They never asked me if I was hungry. They never asked me if I had money. Do you need to Eat. And they would feed me and they wouldn't feed me crap either. It wasn't yesterday's bread or a peanut butter and jelly sandwich. It was a heaping to go container of the best foods that they like. But I remember one time this guy said, let me get you some food, you look hungry. And I was like, I'm so hungry. And he brought me food and he brought me an entire picture of water to sit and drink. Cause it was not the best day and I needed a lot of water.

voice_to_text: Man charged with murdering a 14 year old boy during the Hainault sword rampage is a mystic who dressed up as Robin Hood to play archery weeks before attack. Marcus Arduini Monzo, 36, appeared at Westminster Magistrates Court accused of Daniel's murder along with two counts of attempted murder, two counts of grievous bodily harm, aggravated burglary and possession of a bladed article. Four others were injured during Tuesday's 22 minute rampage, including a heroic female police officer who almost lost a hand. Manzo is an amateur musician and self described mystic who dressed up as Robin Hood for an archery game weeks before the attack, flanked by three burly male DOC officers and one female. The dual Spanish Brazilian national wore a prison issue grey tracksuit and held his left hand over his chest for the entire seven minute hearing. When asked to confirm his full name, he responded very slowly my full name as of my recollection it is Marcus Arielo Audini. Manzo is also accused of bursting into a home where a couple were asleep with their four year old daughter and attacking her father during the rampage, the court heard. David Burns, prosecuting, said Manzo allegedly drove a van at speed at Donato E. Wooley, who was walking on the street, before exiting the vehicle and slashing him around the neck, leaving an injury that required hospital treatment. Manzo then forced entry into the bedroom of a couple who were sleeping with their four year old Child and slash the father in the neck, the prosecutor said. Mr. Burns said he was shouting, if you do not believe in god, he will cause you harm, the prosecutor added. He has then left the scene and attacked Daniel Anjerin, a schoolboy, on his way to school. It is alleged that he stabbed him in the neck and chest. The court heard that while officers were tending to Daniel's injuries, Manzo appeared from a bush and attacked a female police officer with the weapon while she was on the ground.
